 do I spend my time thinking about?  EverQuest of course! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In my infinite wisdom (or lack there of), I came up with a fun little idea that I would like to suggest.<br>
<br>
Let's create two guilds called 'Freeport Army' and 'Qeynos Army'.  Vote on who should start and lead each of the two guilds.  The guilds would not be actual guilds that people stay in, and infact the only people that would be full time members of either guild are the two leaders.<br>
<br>
Then once a month the two leaders meet in West Commons for the following ceremony:<br>
<br>
The leader of the Freeport Army and the leader of the Qeynos Army meet each other at the Druid ring in West Commons.<br>
<br>
Both leaders bow before one another.<br>
<br>
Leader of Freeport Army shouts, &quot;Let it be known on this day, at this time, and for ever more that the Freeport Army offers a challenge of arms to the Qeynos Army.&quot;<br>
<br>
Leader of Qeynos Army shouts, &quot;Your challenge is accepted good sir.  Collect your forces for we charge in to battle in exactly 30 minutes.&quot;<br>
<br>
Leader of Freeport Army shouts, &quot;May the best man win!&quot;<br>
<br>
Both leaders bow before one another, turn away, and proceed to their camps.<br>
<br>
The leader of the Freeport Army sets up camp along the zone to East Commons, and the leader of the Qeynos Army sets up camp along the West wall of West Commons.<br>
<br>
Leader of Freeport Army shouts, &quot;The Freeport Army is recruiting for war at this time.  Hail me for a guild invite immidiately!  Max level 20 and Player Kill Status ON only!&quot;<br>
<br>
Leader of Qeynos Army shouts,  &quot;The Qeynos Army is recruiting for war at this time.  Hail me for a guild invite immidiately! Max level 20 and Player Kill Status ON only!&quot;<br>
<br>
The two leaders guild invite all those who apply (which would probably be a regular bunch of people that enjoy doing this once a month anyway).<br>
<br>
The two Armys buff and prepare for war.<br>
<br>
At the chosen time of war, the two guild leaders declare guild war, and sound the charge...<br>
<br>
WAR is engaged between the two sides for the next couple hours or so until one side concedes defeat.  The two sides drink a lot of alcohol, make fun of each other, and just generally have fun for a while longer... then the closing ceremony is started.<br>
<br>
The leader of the losing army shouts, &quot;We have fought well this day my friends, and you have all fought with honor!  We concede to the Army of (winning army goes here) this day of (date goes here), but we shall return to fight another day...&quot;<br>
<br>
The leaders of the two guilds guild remove everybody but themselves and log off to go play their real characters or what not.<br>
<br>
Let me know if anybody is interested in doing this idea.<br>
